@page "/solutions/customer-success"
@layout MarketingLayout

<PageTitle>NavTour for Customer Success &mdash; NavTour</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="NavTour helps customer success teams build self-serve onboarding libraries, reduce time-to-value, and cut the recurring enablement calls that slow down every CS motion." />
</HeadContent>

<section class="nt-page-hero">
    <div class="nt-container">
        <span class="eyebrow">Solutions &middot; Customer Success</span>
        <h1>Onboarding that customers<br />complete <em>without a call.</em></h1>
        <p class="lead">Replace the 10-session enablement playbook with a self-serve NavTour library. Customers learn at their own pace, CSMs track completion, and time-to-value drops.</p>
        <div class="nt-hero-actions">
            <a href="/register" class="btn btn-orange btn-lg">Start free &rarr;</a>
            <a href="/solutions" class="btn btn-outline btn-lg">All use cases</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="nt-frames-section">
    <div class="nt-container">
        <article class="nt-frame-row">
            <div class="nt-frame-copy">
                <div class="num">01<span class="slash">/</span><span class="lbl">Self-serve onboarding</span></div>
                <h3>Replace 10 onboarding calls with<br /><em>one self-serve hub.</em></h3>
                <p>Build a NavTour library for every workflow your customers need to learn — setup, daily tasks, admin settings, integrations. Customers complete onboarding at their own pace and CSMs spend time on strategy, not feature explanations.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Demo Hub organized by onboarding stage or role</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Bilingual EN/ES onboarding for Americas customers</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Step completion tracking per customer workspace</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="nt-frame-visual">
                <span class="nt-frame-cap">Onboarding hub &middot; self-serve</span>
                <div class="nt-frame-img">
                    <img src="/images/shots/hub.png" alt="Self-serve onboarding hub" class="nt-lightbox" />
                </div>
                <div class="anno tl">
                    <div class="lbl">Time-to-value</div>
                    <strong>Customers progress without waiting</strong>
                    <p>No calendar invite needed. They complete the tour at 9 PM if that&rsquo;s when they have time.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>

        <article class="nt-frame-row reverse">
            <div class="nt-frame-copy">
                <div class="num">02<span class="slash">/</span><span class="lbl">Feature adoption</span></div>
                <h3>New features get <em>used</em>,<br />not just announced.</h3>
                <p>Ship a NavTour with every feature release targeted at existing customers. Embed it in the release email, the in-app notification, and the knowledge base. Customers see the workflow — adoption follows.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>From capture to published demo in 15 minutes</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Embed in Intercom, Zendesk, or any in-app messaging tool</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Analytics on which features customers actually explored</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="nt-frame-visual">
                <span class="nt-frame-cap">Feature release &middot; adoption demo</span>
                <div class="nt-frame-img">
                    <img src="/images/shots/editor.png" alt="Feature adoption demo for customers" class="nt-lightbox" />
                </div>
                <div class="anno bl">
                    <div class="lbl">Adoption loop</div>
                    <strong>Show, don&rsquo;t announce</strong>
                    <p>Customers who watch the walkthrough adopt the feature at 3&times; the rate of those who only read the release note.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>

        <article class="nt-frame-row">
            <div class="nt-frame-copy">
                <div class="num">03<span class="slash">/</span><span class="lbl">Renewal prep</span></div>
                <h3>Renewal reviews that show<br /><em>value, not just slides.</em></h3>
                <p>Build a personalized NavTour for each renewal conversation — highlight the workflows the customer actually uses, the features they&rsquo;ve adopted, and the workflows they haven&rsquo;t tried yet. Champions use it to make the internal case.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Showcase with customer-specific usage highlights</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Forward-able link for internal stakeholder sharing</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Engagement tracking so CSMs know who reviewed it</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="nt-frame-visual">
                <span class="nt-frame-cap">Renewal showcase &middot; personalized</span>
                <div class="nt-frame-img">
                    <img src="/images/shots/showcases.png" alt="Renewal showcase for CS" class="nt-lightbox" />
                </div>
                <div class="anno tr">
                    <div class="lbl">Renewal prep</div>
                    <strong>Value-led, not slide-led</strong>
                    <p>Champions forward the showcase. Decision makers self-serve the story.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>

<NtCTABand Headline="Cut your onboarding call count in half this quarter."
           SubText="Free to start. Build your first onboarding hub before end of the week."
           PrimaryLabel="Start free &rarr;"
           SecondaryLabel="See all solutions"
           SecondaryHref="/solutions" />
